<subSubSection id="C3196578FF93FFC25C89FDF78AB70EC2" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC36F3FF93FFC25C89FDF78AB70EC2" blockId="2.[166,1225,372,760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from the combination of yellow frons (above lunule), parafacial and gena, white microtrichose black propleuron, black postpronotal lobe and notopleural triangle, and one pair of dorsocentral setae. Sternite 6 of male has 2 well sclerotized “teeth” medially on posterior margin (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B02FF93FFC25FC6FD578AC30EC2" author="Rochefort, S. &amp; Wheeler, T. A." box="[916,1213,733,760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" pagination="229 - 240" refId="ref4320" refString="Rochefort, S., Wheeler, T. A. Diversity of Piophilidae (Diptera) in northern Canada and description of a new Holarctic species of Parapiophila McAlpine // Zootaxa. - 2015. - 3925 (2). - P. 229 - 240." type="book chapter" year="2015">Rochefort, Wheeler 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
